<p><placeName>Colorado </placeName><date when="1824-07-25">25th July 1824</date>.</p>
<p><persName>Colo Austin</persName></p>

<p>Sir <persName>Mr. Bell</persName> has in his possession my note for five mules which
are for your benefit&#8212;I pd you $40. which discharged two of them
<persName>Robert Kuykendall</persName> told me he paid you one more and as it is high
time I had lifted the note which I am anxious to do I send you the<pb n="859"/>
order on him for the enclosed act. which I must trouble you to 
present. I am too unwell to wride over and whatever may be lacking I
will settle with you in a short time.</p>

<p><persName>Aylett C. Buckner</persName>.</p>


        </div1>
